<i>adverb</i>: 일정히 [일쩡히], 또박또박 [또박또박], 꼬박꼬박 [꼬박꼬박] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>일정히 [일쩡히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. uniformly</dd><br>
<dd>여럿의 크기, 모양, 시간, 범위 등이 하나로 정해져서 똑같이.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of several things being the same in size, shape, temporal period, range, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>2. constantly</dd><br>
<dd>여럿의 양, 성질, 상태, 계획 등이 변하지 않고 한결같이.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of an amount, quality, state, plan, etc., being unchanging.</dd><br>
<dd>3. regularly; systematically</dd><br>
<dd>전체적인 흐름이나 절차가 규칙적으로.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of an overall flow or procedure being regular.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>또박또박 [또박또박]</dt><br>
<dd>1. neatly; clearly</dd><br>
<dd>말이나 글씨 등이 분명하고 또렷한 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner that a remark or handwriting, etc., are clear and distinct.</dd><br>
<dd>2. regularly; punctually</dd><br>
<dd>규칙이나 차례 등을 한 번도 어기지 않고 지키는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of following a rule, order, etc., without violating it.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>꼬박꼬박 [꼬박꼬박]</dt><br>
<dd>regularly; faithfully</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일을 한 번도 빠뜨리지 않고 계속하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of continuously doing something without skipping it even once.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>